long_desc.thetext:
I saw an issue report on StackOverflow:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24294316/how-can-i-make-qooxdoo-virtual-list-scalable

The use reports that the scrolling is slow when the virtual list has a huge size. This is the code to reproduce the issue:
//create the model data, 1mil items
var rawData = [];
for (var i = 0; i < 1e6; i++) {
  rawData[i] = "Item No " + i;
}
var model = new qx.data.Array(rawData);

//create the list
var list = new qx.ui.list.List(model);
this.getRoot().add(list);

I could find the impact. The source runtime check on __bindEventToProperty took a long time. The impact is only on a source version, but it would be good if it would be possible to improve the check so that the source version works without a huge performance impact.
